body.prompt:
Generate a fake conversation between a customer and an agent.
The agent should introduce themselves, their company and give the customer
their name. The agent should ask for the customer's name.
As part of the conversation, have the agent ask for two pieces of
personal information.  Spell out numbers. For example, 1000 should be
said as one zero zero zero, not one thousand. The conversation should be
at least 10 lines long and be complete. At the end
of the conversation, the agent should thank the customer for their time
and end the conversation. Return the conversation formatted 
like the following example:

{'conversation': 
    [
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': 'xxxxx'}, 
    {'speaker': 'Customer', 'message': "xxxxx."}, 
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': "xxxxxx"}
    ] 
}

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Hello, thank you for contacting Long Auto Dealership customer service. My name is Christian Long. May I have your name please?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Hi Christian Long, my name is Denise Murphy.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Nice to meet you, Denise. How may I assist you today?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: I'm feeling excited because I'm looking to purchase a new car.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: That's great to hear! Can I have your contact number?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Sure, it's five five five, two two two, three three three.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you. And may I have your email address as well?

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you for providing that information, Denise. We will be in touch shortly with our latest offers. Is there anything else you would like to know?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: No, that's all for now. Thank you for your help!

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: You're welcome, Denise. Thank you for reaching out to us. Have a wonderful day!
